				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>Open dialog for SOE/Brenlo and the state of Rangers</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#333300" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brenlo was kind enough to stop by (much appreciated my friend) and had the following post. In it he essentially asks for our feedback on a few items. Please use this thread for that dialog. This is not the place for you to bitch at SOE for their board policies, their stance regarding posting on third party sites or any other wild tangents. It is for discussing the items he addressed in his post. <br />
<br />
I highly encourage thoughtful and spirited debate on this, but please respect the few rules I have in this place regarding personal attacks, profanity, etc. It is fine to argue with people, trying to prove your point and stating your opinion; but keep the kiddie insults, the name-calling, etc out of this or you will be removed.<br />
<br />
Thank you for respecting those few rules. <br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Brenlo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">This was not directed towards you at all Summoon, more to the Rangers that post on the EQ Live boards. They currently are very divided and very vocal and hostile towards each other and my team. While a certain amount of angst is to be expected and even tolerated, some are carrying things to the extreme.<br />
<br />
Now that aside, there are no plans to nerf archery folks. The current plan is to focus on ranger melee. So in the context of melee, what would you like to see added changed, poked and prodded? Please do not say,"We want Rogue DPS" as that is not a reasonable change. To grant you rogue DPS would mean that we would need to take away much of your utility.<br />
<br />
I think that a rangers strong point is its versatility, that they have much to offer and are not confined to one small role. Yet, I hear from many of you that you would like to sacrifice some of that versatility to gain DPS or defense etc . . . So what would you sacrifice to gain more of something. What is the tradeoff? And that presents the question, are you not losing some of what makes a ranger different by becoming more like another class, say rogues ( which I use as it is the most often used class for comparisons to the DPS rangers would like.) Would that not just make you a rogue? Then why play a ranger? Why not make a rogue in the first place? No, I am not saying that you should all go make rogues, although I am sure some of you will say I did. What I am saying is that the more you struggle to become like another class, the less you are a separate class. The less you are rangers and I am not sure that is what you truly want either.<br />
<br />
So what is it you truly want? Is it to be Legolas or Drizzt Do'Urden? Those are great characters in literature but don't really fit well into an MMO. Everyone has to have a role in an MMO and no one class can be a "superclass", now I do know that everyone thinks that there are superclasses but in the grand scheme of things, there is no one class that is more "Uber" than any other. They may be better at specific things but they have their weaknesses as well. So where do you want rangers to fit in?<br />
<br />
So the problem we face, both you the ranger community and I, the guy who tries to represent your interests here (Yes that is what I do) is defining what you want and what you are willing to lose to gain it. I, personally, think rangers are fine. I think they are fun. No, I have not played a ranger to 65 with hundreds of AAs but I have played one. So now I ask you, do you have fun playing a ranger? If not, why? Please no responses equating you to another class. No, I don't have fun because I do less DPS or I parse lower than a warrior. Parse your fun log (yes I know there is no actual fun log, but there should be) and tell me what makes the ranger class fun and what does not. Once we have determined that, then we can figure out where to poke and prod.<br />
<br />
Thanks folks and thanks for reading this long winded post.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
