 <br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11276" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11276</a><br />
 <br />
Basically, I was saying that given what the devs have told us, our sustained DPS will be coming from melee and should be a solid third behind Rogues and Monks. However, to keep archery relevant and especially given that we already have Trueshot, they should use archery to make us the masters of burst damage. That way, there would be a clear melee focus overall that doesn't usurp the dominance of the other classes, but both skills would still have an important role in our class definition and we would have a specific function that makes us a desirable addition to groups.<br />
 <br />
- RD</div>
			
		</td>
