<b>I appreciate your feedback, I really do.  <br />
 <br />
Now, I did try to start a discussion on definition.  I posted that we were now going to focus on melee as part of the ranger definition and knowing that, where would you like to see the class go.  <br />
 <br />
I was met with this kind of response.  You also misunderstand my role, I do not write class definitions, I do not make changes to your class.  I pass along concerns, concerns that are well thought out and well written.  I pass along any responses I get to the community.  Depending on how things are going, responses and changes can take time.  There is nothing I can do about that.  It is an unfortunate aspect of our busy schedules.  Most days, I do not even get to post much, and I apologize for that as well.  We have lots going on and the fact that you may not hear from me or a member of my team does not mean we are ignoring you or have lost interest, simply that we are busy.  <br />
 <br />
Today I had some open time, so I am spending it here in an attempt to get some good dialogue going.  Some folks are contributing to that, and I thank you.  Let's continue it as I may not have time to post here tomorrow or even again until next week.  But that does not mean that you cannot talk about it, discuss it and share your ideas on where you think your class should be.<br />
 <br />
Besides, if we just did the definitions without your input, you would be even more upset with us.  Wouldn't you?</b><br />
