</div><br />
<br />
<b>We get to those as we can and again, not everything you ask for is going to be changed.  We will be honest as to when something will not be changed and all we ask is that you be reasonable in your response.<br />
 <br />
Remember that the top 10 lists are a list from you of what you would like changed, it does not necessarily follow that we will make that change.  Some of the things on that list are big changes as well, stuff that impacts the game as a whole, such as any change to DPS.  We also want to refine your list a little and you will be hearing from Ashlanne on that soon.  Many of the sub items should be items and right now the list is cluttered.  We would like to work with you to come up with a more focused list.  Although it is your option to leave it as it currently is as well.<br />
<br />
I can tell you know that most of the requested archery changes are not going to happen at this time.  Now it is up to you to decide whether you would like to keep them on that list, or put something else up there.</b><br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Seriana</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Brenlo, <br />
Look, DPS is DPS, whether from a bow or melee weapons. You know that, and we know that. Why SOE feels ranged combat is worse for Rangers than it is for all the casters that fight from well away from the mobs is beyond me. Personally I don't care. And that is with the understanding that my current capabilities with bows will not diminish, as you pointed out.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Look, you guys are supposed to be professional game creators. If you're telling me that you don't have any clue as to what we have been talking about, and less of an idea as to what to do to correct what we see as a problem, then you are really wasting your valuable time.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
<b>Point one, Archery DPS is pretty much risk free. There is virtually no danger to the archer. Melee DPS on the other hand is not. So DPS is not DPS. To have a class that can do rogue damage and generate no agro from a distance is not a good thing for the game. That is what we would have if we were to continue to boost archery DPS.<br />
 <br />
Point Two, we do have ideas and thoughts and stuff is already in the works (no I cannot tell you yet) but does that mean we should not talk to you about it? Would you rather we just made changes? Isn't that what got us here? We are not always going to make changes you like but at least you know that you are being heard and for those folks over on the EQlive boards, even you are being heard, the fact that we do not always respond, does not mean we do not read and pass along the good posts. I do have a clue as to what you all are talking about, a large part of what I am trying to do is make sure you have a clue as to what we are talking about. For example, many say that rangers are "broken" our thougt is that they can make it to the high levels and participate in the very high end of EQ just fine, which means, they are not in fact broken. <br />
 <br />
A big part of the communication issues we are all having, and I have discussed this with the class correspondents at length, is we speak a different language. Broken to you means something entirely different than it does to us. When we read, Spell X is broken because it does not do enough damage, what we might hear is, Spell X does not work the way I want it to, thus I feel it sucks. Had that been presented as, spell X does less damage based on the mana to damage ratio that our other class spells have, well now that is a whole different story and something that our designers can actually look at and measure. It is often hard to measure how much you feel something "Sucks", as I am sure you can imagine.</b><br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
