		<!-- message -->
		<div>Here is what I wrote in that other thread:<br />
<br />
(Sunmoon edit: just copied the post in <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" class="inlineimg" />)<br />
 <br />
I have a differing opinion, Brenlo. I believe that your analysis of the situation has some cause and effect issues and some timing issues out of order.<br />
<br />
Ranger's strong point used to be the versatility, and they had very much to offer. That is true, and those are the "good old days" that many of us would like to return to. However these days are not those days.<br />
<br />
1) There is no versatility in GoD tanking. An emergency patch was required to make Paladins and Shadowknights able to live through combat. So the patch did broaden the number of classes available to tank, but that did not nearly reach down to the chain classes. Ranger tanking in GoD lasts 18-22 seconds, after which we need a Ressurection. We have lower tanking related skills than Rogues and Monks, who are our superiors in DPS.<br />
<br />
2) Versatility includes our spell book. Our Spell book lags behind all other Hybrids.<br />
2a) Buffing. We have one buff which is used by a third of the members of most raids. Only SK's have this worse, and they dont come from a Parent Class which has buffs.<br />
2b) Roots, Snares, and the like. Our roots and snares have worse resist modifyers than other classes which have them. Also, more classes are getting snares than before. This mitigates the value of our Roots and Snares.<br />
2c) Damage spells, Direct and Over Time. These spells still reduce our overall DPS when cast, even assuming no resist, and get resisted most of the time. There was a pre-OOW tuning of the total damage of most of the OOW versions, but if the casting time is still so long, and the resist modifier is still non existant, our Damage spells will still be of no benefit to most of the class.<br />
2d) Harmony. Harmony. Again, Harmony. for three-plus years, Druids and Rangers were the only classes with Harmony-type spells. Then other classes got them. Then you take it away from us? Rangers cannot harmony level 66+ mobs. even Monks can, for crying out loud. Besides being able to Feign off any pull-mistakes, they get Lulls to keep from making them in the first place. Why has the core of our pulling versatility evaporated?<br />
<br />
3) Archery. I know there are many problems as SoE sees it with Archery. I know that SoE has never explicitly stated that Archery was a primary form of damage, even though influences congregated for a while to make it the best damage we had available, so I'm not one who says that SoE waffled on this issue. However I will say that Archery made us relatively unique, and it's a shame to see that there have been no substantial increases in it for four expansions, and that during that time melee weapons have seen very substantial increases. No, Archery hasnt been nerfed, but the world has outgrown it. Melee, Dual Wield specifically is to be our "set up of choice for all encounters". That doesnt sound so versitile, does it?<br />
<br />
<br />
So I ask you Brenlo, what's the tradeoff? You've already taken away all of that versatility. We have actually less utility than Monks or Rogues, so-called straight-melee classes. Why is "we want Rogue DPS" a verboten want when Rogues and Monks have accumulated as much versatility as we ever had.<br />
<br />
<br />
My vote is to give us back that utility. Dont 'nerf' anyone else, dont dramatically re-make the Ranger class into a "stand behind the MoB and slash for DPS" single-dimension class. Make us again the number 4 tank. Let us again choose between ranged attack and melee, at a decent risk versus reward ratio for each. Put us a bit behind the DPS leaders, but ahead of classes that can tank better than us. Let our spell book be valuable again, let us perform all of the roles we used to, and not have roots be resisted and break more often than others. And for gosh sakes give us back Harmony. None of this information is new, and if you can sort through the bile on EQlive boards, you'll find well-written posts with parses and data to back up all of the assertions I've made. I just hope that my long windedness is easier to sort through than bile. Oh, and give us back Harmony. And take away the re-instated Hybrid penalty present in OOW.<br />
<br />
And please give us back Harmony.<br />
<br />
Sincerely,<br />
<br />
Finduillas of Druzzil Ro.<br />
<br />
Edit: I cant believe I forgot to mention Ranger Heals. Thanks, Ghostwise.<br />
 <br />
It's missing some comments about our Healing, and how the dynamics of Grouping do in fact require classes to be balanced if the least beneficial classes dont expect to be left out of groups, but others said that before I did.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
