		<div>Looking at a recent reply in the other thread where Brenlo responded to another poster that no new Harmony was not an oversight by the development team.  <br />
 <br />
This is a perfect example of the utility that has been lost over the years.  If lulls were too powerfull(the reason sighted for the change to harmony into harmony of nature prior to the release of PoP) why have you now given the best lull around to a class with FD?  Since the spell itself trivialized pulling why on earth would it be overpowered in rangers(or druids) hands when we have no escape method.  Not only that HoN can be resisted in contrast to yellow mana lulls.<br />
 <br />
What this leads me to believe is it was a conscious decision to remove rangers from the ranks of pullers.  Since you gave bards FM and they get lulls as well I wonder if the truth is that you wanted to make pulling easier, but again wanted it to be classes other then rangers.<br />
 <br />
