	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#333300" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brenlo.<br />
My character's name is Ulvian Stormweaver <br />
He was born in early 2000. <br />
 <br />
My real life name is Konrad Mazurek.<br />
 <br />
I've been an EQ player for four years on and off, a member of this community for about as many. My on and offs were <b>because</b> of the poor state of my class of choice.<br />
 <br />
You see, many of us chose to stick to a class which became destined to carry the brunt of "useless" jokes for four years now. Not because we expected to be brought to a pedestal or issued a medal for our plight. We play Rangers because we expect to see this class brought to a balance it has been begging for along four years' span.<br />
 <br />
I doubt there is a community more dedicated to its class and playing the said class to its utmost ability than that of Rangers.<br />
 <br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				 I think that a rangers strong point is its versatility, that they have much to offer and are not confined to one small role. 
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>On Versatility:<br />
Versatility in Everquest can be a powerful card, one only needs to look at Bards, Shamen, Enchanters and Beastlords. Their classes are an example of versatility gone right. Their absence or shortage at a raid is very very noticeable.<br />
 <br />
Druids, Rangers, Shadowknights, Paladins are an example of versatility gone wrong (although Paladins to a lesser extent because of their Brell's line)<br />
 <br />
I see no reason why players, people who all pay an equal amount of <a href="http://www.adsrve.com/linkredirect.php?h=16,30287113,interealms.com,1" target="_blank">money</a> on a monthly basis should be excluded from an equal amount of company time put into making their class viable, needed, and who knows, maybe even missed when none of its representatives are around.<br />
 <br />
<b>The underlying problem with balancing Rangers </b>isn't versatility. It isn't the choice between archery and meele. It isn't choosing healing spells over offensive ones. The problem is that Rangers, for better or worse have been broken as a class for over four years now.<br />
To fix Rangers, and make no mistake, the class does need to be fixed, one has to go back in time so to say, and make amends for decisions miscarried earlier.<br />
I'm not playing an angst card here, simple facts.<br />
-For four years now Rangers have without fail been the class who recieved the most slander from other Everquest players. We have been the brunt of the jokes, and flash <a href="http://www.adsrve.com/linkredirect.php?h=19,30287113,interealms.com,1" target="_blank">movies</a> making fun of the class' uselesness.<br />
I am firm in believing that alone should be an indication of how badly Rangers need a fix.<br />
 <br />
<b>On Archery Vs Meele schism.</b><br />
The very reason why there exists a schism between archery and meele isn't flavor, it is not roleplay, or wanting to go afk for 3 minutes during a raid encounter. The reason why this schism came into existance in the first place is because with introduction of Archery Mastery 3, and Endless Quiver, Rangers as a class experienced a brief reneissance. <br />
We became requested by raids and groups, we did damage subpar to Rogues and Monks (without discipline active) and every 72 minutes we came close, if not surpassed Rogues and Monks under their disciplines, even though theirs have much shorter reuse times.<br />
 <br />
<b>What can be done to fix Rangers</b><br />
Utility and Dps need to come to balance. Beastlords offer Dps subpar to rogues, and utility spells inferior to their parent class. But they offer things which their parent class can not, nor that can be offered by another one.<br />
Those two things being their mana regen buffs, and their group/MGB mana/hitpoint heals. <br />
This example should be kept in mind when fixing Rangers. Our Dps is sadly lacking for the amount of utility we offer to raids and groups, our durability is far behind the ratio between utility and dps. This all makes for a class which is sub-par in about every aspect of its gameplay and world mechanics, other than being voted most likely to run the most corpse runs.<br />
 <br />
Everyone has their niche, besides Rangers. It used to be said that we have the best attack buffs, but considering Paladin Brell series has become the class favourite, those attack buffs are no longer the niche we need.<br />
Not even an ability as baseline as Tracking is our true niche, because Tracking, in all truth is equivalent in importance to any tradeskill. <br />
 <br />
<b>Rangers need badly the following things.</b><br />
<b>-</b>Substantial DPS increase from meele.<br />
-Slight DPS increase from offensive spells.<br />
-Slight increase in buff utility<br />
-Substantial increase in raid utility<br />
-Slight increase in durability.<br />
 <br />
Dps Increase<br />
 <br />
Ranger meele should be close to monks. Pure meele alone, given the fact monks bring FD pulling and indoor lull. Abilities which make and break raids in some cases. We should be given a true meele discipline which does not run on a 72 minute timer. We have been called a Dps class for years now, while our Dps has never been good enough.<br />
 <br />
Our offensive spells are far too easily resisted in both. The raid, and the group settings. Most high end rangers report that it causes their Dps to go down when they excercise Direct Damage spells as an option.<br />
 <br />
I suggest they all be brought up by 15-20% in total damage, as well as have their casting times lowered, as per Rangers being through years now, a dual wielding class. I would like to humbly suggest a cast time of maximum, 1.0 seconds at level 60, scaling down to 0.5/0.3 seconds by level 70. The resistances should likewise be adjusted.<br />
 <br />
One might claim nukes in range of 612-1000 are a lot of "one hit" damage. <br />
One must also consider though. They all have recast times, they all have a fizzle chance. All those nukes cost mana, which is a very finite resource, especially when it comes to sustaining self buffs, throwing Call of Rathe, etc.<br />
Finally one should consider how much exactly DO rogues dash out in one-shots. Backstabs in excess of 2000 have been in existance since SoL, if not earlier.<br />
 <br />
Furthermore, I suggest Rangers be offered the planar (PoP) levels of Spell Critical Fury. Our parent class gets this AA, Shadowknights and Beastlords both get their parent classes' AA from GoD which opens DoT spells to crit. I think that suggests a precedence for Rangers to be given an old Alternate Ability which we should have had since the very beginning.<br />
 <br />
Buff Utility.<br />
Mana Regeneration, Hp Regeneration, Hp Buffs, AC Buffs and the like already have their parent classes. I would like to suggest Rangers be granted an overhaste buff spell of a small %. 15-20% seems in line (I would like this one up for discussion from other community members)<br />
 <br />
Substantial Raid Utility Increase<br />
Beastlords get Mana/Hp restoration. Shamen get slows, Paladins get Brells, and so on. Rangers would be well suited as an offensive assistance niche. Which your developement team began to adress with Auspice of The Hunter. Which ability has sadly been downgraded as of late.<br />
I would like to suggest Auspice be restored to its original 75 attk, in the slot 6 spot, and its duration increased back to 1 minute. Also I'd like to entertain the possibility it grants a small mana regen to its targets. 6-10 mana/tick or such rough figure.<br />
 <br />
Durability Increase.<br />
As a Dps class, our only means of shedding aggro for the past years has been jolt, a spell. Increase in Hp via simple means would seem well suggested. Please open to us the option of Planar Durability (PoP AA) as well as increase our avoidance/mitigation slightly (I do know this would have to be fine tuned)<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Far as what we would be willing to give up.<br />
 <br />
..well there are a few sensless spells in our repertoire.<br />
Swarm series anyone?<br />
 <br />
 <br />
<b>In Closing</b><br />
This all might seem like a lot of work, and I acknowledge it is. But please entertain what I've stated before. Rangers have been badly in need of an overhaul by the time Scars of Velious came around. This given how poorly we already fared in Kunark with changes introduced by that expansion. For all concerns the Defensive increases given to us in Velious should have come prepackaged with Kunark.<br />
 <br />
The Ranger class has been badly in need of an overhaul for nearly half a decade now. SoE inherited critical mistakes in decision making in terms of balancing our class from Verrant Interactive. <br />
 <br />
I urge you Brenlo, to help us recieve this virtual justice we have been denied for a span of years now.<br />
 <br />
I assure you many Rangers such as myself will come out of retirement on that note.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
