		<!-- message -->
		<div>OK, this has been posted numerous times already, but here goes:<br />
<br />
Melee DPS : Triple attack or similar boost and melee disciplines please (a burst discipline on a reasonable timer). We are looking to be behind rogues and monks but not so far behind as we are now.<br />
 <br />
DD Spells: Cut recast times on DDs hugely so we can use our mana. Give them resist adjustments so they can land. <br />
 <br />
Dots: Take them - I don't care<br />
 <br />
DD vs Summoned: Take them also<br />
 <br />
Harmony: We need the druid spell.<br />
 <br />
Aggro shedding: An FM-like ability (Cover Tracks?) <br />
 <br />
Snare and root: Resist adjustments. Fast cast versions (can be reduced duration on snare if need be).<br />
 <br />
This is about <b>restoring</b> our versatility.<br />
 <br />
Then look at our top 10. Some will have been fixed. Some will remain (such as heals and fixing our buffs so they don't get overwritten. This adds to our fun by removing the un-fun stuff <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" class="inlineimg" /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
