		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brenlo, it has been stated before but I reiterate.  Fun is not being LFG for hours on end.  Fun is not being able to get a XP group because you can bot a shaman outside the group.  During the early days of PoP, the only way I could get a XP group w/o EQ/AM3 was by bringing a shaman out of group.  Sadly, with the release of OoW, those days are back.  <br />
 <br />
 The changes that the ranger community are asking for in no way redefine who we are.  Unlike other classes (and yes, other classes need to be looked at since they have recieved our abilities while giving up nothing), we are asking for nothing new.  We are only asking for an extension of abilities we currently have.  <br />
 <br />
 Snare and Root: A new high level snare and root w/ a resist mod.  When my guild is clearing Time, there is no reason a Berserker should be able to snare Vallon Zek splits w/o a resist while I have every snare resisted and recieve a free trip to bind because of it.  This is one of our key abilities that has been farmed out to another class who can now do it better.<br />
 <br />
 Harmony:  Personally, I dont agree with those who have asked for a indoor harmony line.  That is a new ability, something we havn't had before.  Shortly after PoP, the original Harmony was nerfed and Harmony of Nature was added.  Now that wasnt a bad thing.  But HoN was not capped at mobs 5 levels below our level cap.  Why is this allowed in OoW with a level 70 cap?<br />
 <br />
 Heals: They are woefully inadequite in current content, even on downtime healing.  I should need to spend 30AA on healing just so my heal spell can heal for th same as one hit from a mob in GoD.  I have close to a 7k mana pool raid buffed.  A heal that does 1k+ base for 900+ mana would be worth using.<br />
 <br />
 DPS:  At the end of the day, when a group is put together, it all comes down to this.  SoE has decided to focus on melee DPS for a ranger.  That is fine and at least we understand where you intend to go with us.  Now warrior with similar weapons to us with the same AA's and Atk will do more DPS then use.  This is due to there innate triple attack.  Can you explain to me what purpose a ranger has on a raid with a limited number of spots?  If a warrior can match our DPS, why not bring more warriors and just have a token ranger along for buffing?  We do not want Rogue DPS (if I'm not mistaken, Berserkers are asking for this).  We do not want Monk DPS.  But we surely want to do significantly more then a warrior.  Additinally, when a rogue parses doing 2x the DPS as a ranger using their only damage disc, somethin is very out of balance.<br />
 <br />
 Tanking abilities:  In a perfect world, rangers would avoid damage worse then a monk yet mitigate better then them.  They would avoid damage better then a plate tank yet mitigate worse.  They would mitigate and avoid damage better then any other chain class.  The would have better defensive abilities then a pure offensive class.  <br />
 <br />
 Summoned spell line:  Honestly, this whole spell line is crap.  Can you give us any justification to use a proc buff only usefull on summoned creatures?  My personal opinion is that Rythen migrated our PoP spell line and then forgot about it.  With the active removal of summoned creatures from the game, this spell line is worthless to every ranger I have talked to.  I believe continual inclusion of this spell line is a direct result of having no high level, high AA rangers on the class balance/development team.  <br />
 <br />
 Forage AA:  I must apologize when I say this but this AA is a insult, a slap in the face to rangers.  This is a AA that was put in so we would have the same number of OoW as other classes yet the devs couldnt think of anything new.  <br />
 <br />
 Tracking: Between SEQ, the druid/bard track bug, nerfed tacking ranges; the benefit of this utility has been severly reduced.  This is a core ability has deminished in value while rangers have recieved nothing in return.<br />
 <br />
 If anything I have brought up is a change/expansion of our abilities into other class areas, please let me know.  Those who are posting here have the same goal, to see the the problems that rangers have are resolved fairly.<br />
 <br />
 Now, I going mention something rather self serving.  Sunmoon also runs the Shamans Crucible.  Shaman were told months ago there that they were not being ignored by a Sony Rep on the Crucible.  And they were promplty ignored.  Shaman also need some care, they need to have some balance focusing.  With them though it will be more difficult because there core abilities have been farmed out to other classes.</div>
