		<!-- message -->
		<div>in responce to one of brenlo's answers<br />
 <br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				 <br />
"<br />
<i>This is the part that cracks me up, what dont you understand?</i><br />
 <br />
<i>*WE HAVE ALREADY GIVEN UP ALOT OF OUR UTILITY TO OTHER CLASSES*</i><br />
 <br />
<i>Berserker: Instant cast, reduced resist snare, instant stun, group attack buffs</i><br />
<i>Monk, bard, druid: Harmony</i><br />
<i>Nuking: Beastlord, SK</i><br />
 <br />
<i>This is just the *very* begining of what we gave up/sacrificed, and are still waiting to see *some* sort of benefit."</i><br />
 <br />
<b>So you lost it? I do believe you still have it, it is just shared now. Again, I am not saying that you have to sacrifice anything for some small adjustments, nor should you. All I am asking you, is not to ask for the sky, you stand a much better chance for change, if you ask for small reasonable things. If/when those are changed, you perhaps ask for more small reasonable changes. </b><br />
 <br />
<b>I may not know everything, and according to some I don't know much (grins) but I do know that if you ask for the moon, you ain't gonna get it.</b>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>no, we didn't "lose it", however our outdoor only harmony was nerfed because "an unresistable harmony was overpowered", yet after ours was nerfed monks got an unresistable usable anywhere harmony ability, now I don't see how a hybrid who is suposed to be able to cast spells it's overpowered, but for a pure melee who isn't suposed to have spells it isn't, this is also one of the examples at why hybrids in general are underpowered, hybrids gave up other abilities for spells, but now pure melees have their own spells via the yellow mana, aka stamina and didn't give up anything.<br />
 <br />
snare, we were one of the original snarer classes, but now a pure melee class, beserkers, can snare better than us with a zero cast time snare, again rangers gave up lots of melee skills for our spells which melees who gave up nothing are getting better.<br />
 <br />
nuking, ok out of the 4 hybrids 3 of us have access to nuke lines, rangers, SK's, and beastlords, rangers are hybrids of druids, SK's are hybrids of necro's, beastlords, are hybrids of shamans, out of the 3 parents druids are by far the best nuker, distantly followed by necro and then shamans.<br />
 <br />
top nukes of the parent classes and the percentage the other parent classes are to druids.<br />
druid: 2302 damage, cast time 6.35, raw DPS 365.5<br />
necro: 1788 damage, cast time 6.0, raw DPS 298 (81.5% of druids)<br />
shaman: 1272 damage, cast time 7.8, raw DPS 163.1 (44.6% of druids)<br />
 <br />
ok, now top nukes of the 3 hybrids based off them and the other hybrids percentage to rangers, now if rangers were properly balanced the percentages should be roughly the same as the parent classes.<br />
ranger: 1039 damage, cast time 3.5 (1.8 with hybrid haste), raw DPS 577.2<br />
SK: 928 damage, cast time 0.5, raw DPS 1856 (321.6% of rangers)<br />
beastlord: 1002 damage, cast time 3.2 (1.6 with hybrid haste), raw DPS 626.3 (108.5% of rangers)<br />
 <br />
see something wrong with that picture, parents druid>necro>shaman, hybrids SK>beastlord>ranger, then to top it off rangers actualy gain the least benifit from our nukes as you can't melee during the cast time so the actual gained damage from a nuke is the nukes damage minus what you would have done if you did cast and just melee, rangers have the highest raw melee and the lowest spell DPS, SK's have slightly lower raw melee DPS and the highest spell DPS, also since they use slow 2h weapons they can easily cast between swings and not lose any melee damage, beastlord have even lower raw melee DPS because a parger percentage of their damage comes from their pet who doesn't have to stop meleeing when they are casting, ranger's nukes are such poor DPS in relation to our melee DPS than given the top weapons and nukes of a given expansion and the resist rates our nukes at best come out as a wash, and can actualy lower our damage. <br />
 <br />
the better weapons a ranger gets the worse our nukes get in terms of added value, the fix is very simple, the casting time needs to be changed to 0.5 seconds like SK's, that way our nukes actualy are worth casting high end, and don't actualy get worse with better gear, this fix alone would mostly or even entirely fix the ranger DPS problem as the reason our damage is slow low is end game we are nothing more than warriors as our spells (nukes + dots) don't actualy add to our damage as intended.<br />
 <br />
the same issues with nukes goes for our heal as well, druids direct heal is significantly better than shamans yet beastlords can heal just as well as us, buffs as well, our hp buff line doesn't scale to our parents at the same rate as other hybrids, ours also took a significant nerf aside from the hp not being high enough as we should have the mana regen componets of the druid lines now but we got hp regen instead which is basicaly useless.<br />
 <br />
other stuff:<br />
 <br />
atk buffs, they were great when added, now we have hit the soft cap and atk hardly does anything anymore, they need to be changed to a raw +min damage mod and + damage mod to give the equivilant boost they did before we starting hitting the soft caps so they scale properly high end.<br />
 <br />
melee, ok, finanly the official focus is on melee which is always should have been IMO, rangers are currently the <b>only</b> melee class in the game who doesn't have an offensive disc based off our primary form of damage, we need a damage disc for our melee added as it's an insult imo to say we are a melee class and ment to melee all the time but our disc is for an alternate lower skill, all hybrids should have 1 disc added for OoW imo, pure melees got 3, 1 for each hybrid isn't unreasonable to ask for imo.<br />
 <br />
OoW AA's, ok this is simply ahuge insult to ranger, other classes get usefull stuff like critical dots, what do we get? critical forage, I mean really, this is without a doubt the worse and most useless AA in the game, inate cha is more usefull and that's one of our class specific AA's, really get rid of it and give us something usefull, heck the dot crit AA like all the other hybrids who can cast dots would be nice, well assuming our dots are ever fixed as for damage added our dots are even worse than our nukes.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
