<tr valign="top">
	<td class="alt2" width="175">
			
			<div id="postmenu_617543">
				
				<a class="bigusername" href="member.php?s=f4e5389be136e78c8cf535687961a58e&amp;u=25451">Uinan_Ranger</a>
				<script type="text/javascript"> vbmenu_register("postmenu_617543", true); </script>
				
			</div>
			
			<div class="smallfont">Member</div>
			
		
			
			
			<div class="smallfont">
				&nbsp;<br />
				<div>Join Date: Jan 2004</div>
				
				
				<div>
					Posts: 63
				</div>
				
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#333300" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Greetings Brenlo,<br />
 <br />
I love my ranger, though it's been the most frustrating class I have ever played.<br />
 <br />
You try to tell us that our versitility is what makes us unable to have higher DPS, but I have to wonder how many have experienced the higher ends of being a ranger? Everything that we have as versitle, can be done much better by other classes. Everything that is our 'unique versatility' is only used when a group or raid simply can't find another class that can't do it better, and more efficently then us.<br />
 <br />
I, like many Rangers, grow sickly tired of going LFG through many zones for HOURS upon  hours. Not asked to a group during prime playtime some times for long periods, because there's many other classes that bring more to the table then a Ranger, or bring what a ranger does, but does so better. <br />
 <br />
I think a lot of rangers, or at least myself, would like to feel a sense of being useful, or needed. to know that people will want my Ranger in their groups, will know what they can do better then other classes and enjoy having it. <br />
 <br />
What is our class defining ability? Some would say Archery, but that is clearly not the direction Rangers is going in.<br />
 <br />
Some would say pulling outdoors, but yet we did not receive a Harmony Upgrade in OoW, but yet Druids do. I may be wrong, but I've not been in a group when some one said, "Oh, let's get a Druid to go pull for us...." <br />
 <br />
Another thing about Pulling is a lot of rangers would like to have some sort of bail-out so to speak of a bad pull. Other pulling classes have such tools, such as a Feign Death, Fading Memories, even a Rogue can wipe agro off of themselves completely. Some of the higher tier zones is much too dangerous when the group has no Mezzer, and a ranger is pulling. a Harmony resist(or now hunting exp mobs higher then lvl 65.) and you are bringing multiple mobs back to a camp that is trying to rely on me to bring single pulls, but I can't, because I have not been given the appropriate tools.<br />
 <br />
What else is our defining characteristic? You spoke about how we, as Rangers, should not try to be like other classes, but how can we not,  when our abilities have been given away to other classes time and time again? How can we not long to have more characteristics of another class, when everything we CAN do, is done better by other classes?<br />
 <br />
It stings when you are LFG for hours, and a group finally says, "Well, we can't find anything else, we'll take the Ranger."<br />
 <br />
It sucks to not be a desired class to have around. To have so much time invested into a character, years of work and energy and money, to only be good enough to use if nothing else is better.<br />
 <br />
What makes us unique really? That we don't do things as well as the other classes? That even out root parking and snap agro was nerfed with the changes to agro on Snare &amp; Flame lick? That we can't even peel mobs away from a group &amp; park it in a root some times? That when we do root it, it lasts 10 seconds? <br />
 <br />
How can we be improved? We've been discussing such for months, and the things most rangers agree on, we're told are not acceptable, what are we left to think? <br />
 <br />
But fine, here's how I think we should be made better.<br />
 <br />
Pulling - We are rangers. We should be the best option to pull outdoors safely then any other class. Why? Because we're rangers! We're always outdoors. What would this entail? Howabout the Harmony upgrade that was given to Druids and NOT rangers? Or an agro loss ability, perhaps an AA like Fading Memories. Something to allow us to abort a bad pull. Perhaps a 5 or so minute re-use timer maybe.<br />
 <br />
Spells - Our spells are weak. Very weak. Only two of our buffs are ever wanted, and even then they are not very important. Our nukes are laughable at best, and I won't even mention our dots.  <br />
 <br />
Melee - Fine. I'm perfectly content to get my greater DPS from melee, but right now that is not the case. Right now My damn bow does slightly more damage then my melee set up, either dual weilding or Two hand slash. Do not require our Melee DPS to out do our Bows, only after requiring insane weapons and a boat load of AA's. Our Melee ability to be third in line in doing damage should be INNATE, regardless of having an uber-weapon or an average weapon. Spending AA's and tons of time raiding is NOT the way to balance a class.<br />
 <br />
Disciplines - Ok, so we are a melee class now. Fine. Then why is our big Damage Disc archery? If we are a melee class, we certainly need a burst damage discipline to use while meleeing that in theory should go beyond our archery &amp; Trueshot, if we are afterall a Melee DPS class.<br />
 <br />
I love my Ranger, but it's certainly not easy to continue as the class. Give us a sense of being useful, of belonging. <br />
 <br />
Uinan<br />
Povar</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
