		<!-- message -->
		<div>Finduillas and Ulvian those are excellent posts. Both said many things I planned on saying, so no point in rehashing them here.<br />
 <br />
I do have to comment about Brenlo's quote repeated in the post just ahead of me by Tilara. I play in a high end guild (tacvi enabled). Take my word for this Brenlo, if I leave the raid people might shrug, if a cleric or warrior or knight or rogue or bard or monk leave the raid people ask questions.<br />
 <br />
On loot awards rangers receive the least priority. Why? Because if a ranger threatened to quit people could care less. Not true with alot of other classes. And that TELLS you something about raid viability.<br />
 <br />
With mudflation the game dumbed down to the point where versatility does not mean what it USED to mean. So it boils down to dps and survivability to win fights more than anything.<br />
 <br />
Ranger has only 3 ways to cause dps: melee, archery and spells. <br />
 <br />
Archery you pretty much killed post POP as a main combat form, not by nerfing it directly, but by nerfing it indirectly (not imporoving it to keep up with the expansion difficulty). <br />
 <br />
Spells, we really only have nukes. I was actually looking forward to lining up 8 nukes eventually and then chain nuking mobs, but it seems the way you set it up we can't, since one greys-out another. So whether a ranger actually gets the next nuke upgrade it isn't really that big a deal since the damage difference between the prior one is not that big.<br />
 <br />
Melee, well basically that puts us square with the rogue/monk. All 3 of us chase the mobs back smacking at it. And since ranger defense is pretty much weak (leather wearing beastlords do a better job), you have FORCED the ranger to play like a rogue/monk.<br />
 <br />
At one time ranger versatility was the best. We could tank, we did great comparative dps, we were GREAT outdoor pullers, we were CCers, we had utility spells that WEREN"T available to all the classes (clickies, effects, and potions killed that). All that is pretty much gone. So now any return to the past, by giving us back what we had will only cause anger amongst the other classes.<br />
 <br />
To be honest, I don't think there is a real solution. At best you can toss us some bones. If you go too far, the other classes will now scream. Archery was your best out. Aside from raw dps numbers, other classes had nothing to compare it with. With melee, all the other classes are going to inevitably compare weapons and bitch.<br />
 <br />
Pointless to make suggestions since you set the parameter which is not acceptable to me or many others I suspect. I am tired of the constant flip flopping of the ranger's role throughout this game's progression.</div>
