				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Brenlo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">You do have the right to voice your complaints but that does not mean we can or should make every change you complain for. We have a responsibility to the 15 other classes as well. As much as you hate any of your abilities being given away, so do they. We want the game to be fun, and believe it or not, most folks (even rangers) are having fun.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>From the legions of complaints, I would argue that point. Something somewhere is broken - and like a thorn in the paw of a lion, is causing the larger system to be disrupted. While there is fun to be had, some people are having less fun all of a sudden - find the reason for that, and fix it so it never breaks again. The challenge of course, is finding a fix that doesn't take away someone else's fun.<br />
 <br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
