		<!-- message -->
		<div>Ok, I'm going to try to make this non confrontational.<br />
I'm very sorry you and your team feel like you have been attacked by the ranger community, before you continue believing this, you should look at the thread that someone started calling for your dismissal and see how many rangers actually supported you, but that's off the point.<br />
 <br />
You stated that for rangers the have rogue dps we must give up most of our utility and that we have not lost many of our abilities, we just share them with other classes now. I ask, did those other classes give up anything to gain that utility? As for not losing abilities, take our harmony as a prime example, we had it nerfed, given to a non casting class, then with the release of the new expansion we got no upgrades to it but the new class did, I'd say we lost some utility, we lost our ability to pull. My post isn't totally accusatory, but is trying to point out that while it good that you believe that ranger dps is lagging, it by your own admission cannot be taken singly and we must consider what and how much utility the ranger class has lost over the years. This directly impacts on the degree to which you would be thinking of upgrading ranger dps. Either restoration of ranger utility or a very sizeable upgrade in dps is in order, it's your game, it's your decision.<br />
 <br />
While we're discussing utility, you are correct in that the ranger class posses a great deal of utility, well it looks good on paper. We have utility, but in many or our day to day situations, most of it is completely useless. One must remember that the ranger class is one that should be group and raid friendly. When grouping, almost every other class brings to the table the same ranger abilities but to a much more effective extent. This is irrevocable damage already done to the ranger class and an attempt to upgrade this old utility would cause much dissent from the classes that possess them. What I believe is needed is a completely ranger type utility. If your intention is to upgrade ranger dps while not infringing on rogue dps, mesh the utility with the dps and share that with our groupmates. You did a decent job with the Auspice of the Hunter AA and the Nature's Veil, the effectiveness was just severly lacking.<br />
 <br />
If rangers are to be forced to melee, we need agro dumping capabilities. Jolt was by far an in large a waste. Archery was the solution to that but since it is going to be a non entity, we need options.<br />
 <br />
You say you have ideas but can't tell us, but you want us to share our ideas. This is going to sound accusatory, but it sounds like you are fishing for ideas for a new expansion or for berserker upgrades. Given the past expansions, I find it really hard to use up my best ideas to be implemented in another class. If you cannot tell us what you ideas are, then at least give us the general direction in which your ideas flow. How familiar is the development team with the ranger class, what I'm asking is that how many of them play rangers on a regular basis in all situations. The reason I ask this is that while you are keeping you ideas secret until release, if you aren't going to tell us, how are we to be ensured that they will be of value to the ranger class. I'm pretty sure someone on the team thought that critical forage was a great idea, but rangers apparently did not. Again that is a prime example of the need for either having somoene extremely familiar with the class on the team or inclusive ranger feedback.<br />
 <br />
While I touched on berserkers, where are they going to stand in relation to rangers. If we are to be melee, they already have the edge on us in terms of tanking and probably will have the edge on 'viable' utility, we should not suffer for the dps.</div>
