			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#333300" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>What made playing Huppen (my ranger) fun?  He could do a bit of everything, each well enough that he came in close enough for groups to say "well, we can't find X for the group (being it cc, tank, puller, emergency healing), but we can grab that ranger, he'll be able to fill in well enough and add dps too"<br />
<br />
What made playing Huppen not fun?  He can still do a little bit of everyting, but not well enough that he can fill in for anything.  he can't tank because he gets wailed on, he can't cc because his snare/root won't land more than 20% of the time against a mob that runs faster than SoE and wails on him, his heals can barely keep up with rampage damage on trash mobs, and his harmony doesn't work on anything over lvl 65, and we can't bring anything else to the group other than dps, which is lagging behind way too many classes.<br />
<br />
What made him fun was that he could fill a variety of needs, now it takes 3 of him to fill that same need because his abilities haven't scaled with the content.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
This is what i would like to see to make us into a duel weild oriented hybrid dps class. Rogues get the massive damage from melee from behind, monks get good damage from almost anywhere. So let us Get our damage from procs, both from an increased proc rate as well as vastly increased damage from procs.<br />
<br />
<br />
Innate<br />
1)triple attack - main hand at 51, off-hand at 60<br />
2)move up a damage table at 65 and again at70<br />
3)increased damage on procs: 5%(lvl51), 10% (lvl55), 20% (lvl60), 35% (lvl65), 50% (lvl70)<br />
<br />
Alternate Advancement<br />
1)Flurry &amp; it's upgrades - replaces precision of the pathfinder and scout's efficiency<br />
2)proc damage aa - increase damage by 30% (lvl 60), 60% (lvl65), 100% (lvl70) - replaces nature's bounty in OoW Tab<br />
3)Weapon Affinity Mastery - doubles the proc rate given by weapon affinity - replaces trackign mastery in OoW tab<br />
4)Ambidexterity Mastery - will no longer fail to make a duel weild skill check - replaces punishing blade in PoP Ability tab<br />
5)the riposte and DS aa from OoW in a mainhand version, doesn't effect pvp. Only up to a maximum of 50% or so though, enough to offset going froma 2 hander to duel weild - replaes flame/frost arrows in GoD tab<br />
5)Augment to our kick ability that reduces agro - replaces Double Riposte in Class tab<br />
6)one to make innate procs trigger from kicks - replaces headshot in PoP Abilities tab<br />
<br />
Spells<br />
1)move the atk component in our multibuff to a slot other than 2 (to stop debuffs from overwriting it), and increase the hp given to be equal to the Brells of that spell set (PotW with 330hp, WotH with 412hp).<br />
2)add a second version of the multibuff spell, with an agro-reducer "Ward of the Hunted" if you will.<br />
3)substantially increase the atk on both of our buff lines, as well as adding a damage modifier to them (to the multibuff as well)<br />
4)increase the power of our proc buffs. Cry of Thunder to 175 base, Call of Lightning to 250 base<br />
5)add a fire and cold version of the Call of Thunder line<br />
6)turn the entire anti-summoned line into a scaling line of jolt spells, with nature's rebuke being an upgraded jolting blades.<br />
7)lower the casting times on our nukes to 0.5 seconds, up the refresh to 45 seconds, and double the mana/damage cost for the ones over lvl60<br />
<br />
Disciplines<br />
1)TS like ability for melee, same re-use, tied to it's timer.<br />
2)Short refresh burst discipline, making every attack possible go off for the next 12 seconds or whatever (full quad with trip on each hand and flurry). Kind of like the rogue Assassin's strike line.<br />
3)Mid refresh disc that makes every possible proc go off for the next 12 seconds.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
