		<div>I've included two posts here from the SOE boards that are stickied under the Ranger Definition forum - I don't understand why we have to have another forum here now.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Ranger Class Lists thread<br />
 <br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=3800" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=3800</a><br />
 <br />
Ranger Spells and Abilities Thread<br />
 <br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=10008" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=10008</a><br />
 <br />
 <br />
2nd of all, this talk of having to tradeoff abilities, not infringing upon other classes and asking us "what is fun" really makes me feel insulted as a customer. Our issues have a consistent theme of lack of scaling for hybrids, especially rangers, as new expansions come out. Whether it's an issue of our buffing line, our nukes, our snares, not getting harmony upgrade, dps that has dwindled over the years, nuke lines that are not good enough - it's about scaling and how it has failed to keep us in balance. We are trying to stay viable, not overpower other classes and especially when so many classes share our abilities there is no reason why they cannot share theirs in some cases.<br />
 <br />
Last of all, and I truly hope that this post is allowed to stand as is, I am very unhappy with the decision for this board to be used as our forum to speak with you. Part of the disconnect among Rangers now (started by the mixed messages the developers have been giving us through the last few expansions) was exacerbated on this board due to the owner of this board not allowing discussions about the state of the game last year when these problems were being more and more noticed by the high-end community. We were basically called elitists, whiners and troublemakers at that time and had to resort to posting to another board to be able to discuss our issues. The SOE boards have been good IMO because issues can be discussed in one place with clear messages coming from the official boards. Now I have to visit a message board that has let me know in the past that my concerns are not valid and don't have a place here.</div>
