		<!-- message -->
		<div>Aluyen, WONDERFUL post.<br />
 <br />
The issue I see with Rangers at this moment is we have no melee skills that differentiate our melee attack from the Warrior. When using nearly identical weapons on the same mob (your arena parsing mob during the OOW beta) A Ranger and Warrior were set up nearly identical. There was nearly no difference in DPS between the Warrior and Ranger when using just weapons (no discs). When the Ranger used his spells (and the Warrior just melee) the Ranger did have an advantage over the Warrior. When the Warrior used his offensive melee discs, the warrior again was equal to the Ranger. (Why are there no melee discs for the Ranger?)<br />
<br />
Now you see my issue. SoE wants rangers to be melee centric. Without any change Rangers provide the DPS of a Warrior but the tanking abilities of a Rogue.<br />
<br />
On raids, we are fighting for spots. The targets usually resist our spells, they can do more damage on one swing than we can heal, and they can chew through our defenses faster than we can be healed. What is our role to be on Raids? Why would it be beneficial for a raid to have more than one Ranger?<br />
<br />
Druids have received an pgrade to Harmony of Nature. Monks have been given a lull, Paladins and Clerics have their lull. Where we were once a highly sought after class for pulling duites, anywhere post BoT we have a very difficult time ding this. Our Harmony won't work on most mobs in GoD, now with a new expansion and an increase in the level of the mobs, a further degredation of a skill that was once our specialty has occured.<br />
<br />
Archery. Where to start there? You said that it does not generate aggro. Why does it not do this? If Archery were generating aggro wouldn't that be a self correcting issue? Offensive casters generate aggro while nuking why doesn't Archery? I think that it is because the Ranger using his bow vs high end mobs is not putting the DPS that is near the rest of the raid, therefore nearly no aggro. <br />
<br />
Remember around level 50 when Rangers were taking aggro from the Warriors when the Ranger was using two fast one-handers, we had to switch to 2hs to keep from becoming Ranger speedbumps. Hit bigger but not nearly as often means lower aggro. Right now Rangers are not hitting as often nor for as much as the rest of the raid. <br />
<br />
I do not think that we need dedicated archery improvements, I do feel that we should have naturally improving bows/arrows as we increase in power would fit many of our Archery needs.<br />
<br />
I feel that the largest problem we have is the Elemental Bows became useable by mostly non-elemental rangers. I admit I had a Stonewood Compound Bow before I reached Elemental Planes. With all the non-elemental rangers going to battle vs non-elemental mobs while the Ranger has an Elemental weapon, the results are tilted seriously in the favor of the Ranger. That is what caused the problem with Archery. Now in Time and beyond we are doing no more damage with our bows than we were from those days in BoT. There has been nearly zero natural progression with that weapon. <br />
<br />
It is said that Ranger Archery is out of balance. How can it be out of balance when Rogues can do more damage non-disc than Rangers can do with Trueshot? Again look at my initial hypothesis about the lack of aggro created by archery due to the increase of the damage and the increased repetition of the rest of the raid's attacks before saying that there is no risk to the Ranger while using Archery.<br />
<br />
Thank you Brenlo for talking to us. Rangers are a special class, we keep seeing how our specialties are being "shared" with other classes so we keep trying to re-develop where we can shine. We don't have much ill-feelings towards you, we know that you are mearly the messenger. We just want to feel like we are a wanted class.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
