<b>Howdy,<br />
<br />
I did mention that rangers do need some poking and prodding, perhaps some upgrades in some key areas, that does not mean that anything will be taken away. However, if rangers were to receive all of the things they want, we would have to remove other abilities. We cannot allow one class to have everything they want, simply because they want it. We then end up with one class. Where is the fun in that? <br />
<br />
You do have the right to voice your complaints but that does not mean we can or should make every change you complain for. We have a responsibility to the 15 other classes as well. As much as you hate any of your abilities being given away, so do they. We want the game to be fun, and believe it or not, most folks (even rangers) are having fun. <br />
<br />
So, would an increase to melee dpw make the game more fun for you? Perhaps some discs or AAs related to dps output? Some of what I see suggests that it would help. Let's hear some more on that point please.</b><br />
<i><font color="sienna">Ok, here you go, reposted from what I had on EQ Live Ranger Definition:</font></i><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Blinding Strikes</font> - (2 4 6)  Pre-Requisite(s):  Level 65-66-67. <font color="lime">Ferocity 3, Precision of the Pathfinder 3</font>.  Your ability to press continued attacks against your opponent often opens up opportunities to strike critical area's.  This AA line gives you a chance to slash your opponent across the eyes, blinding your opponent for 4 ticks.  The chance to land a blinding strike is 3%, 6%, 10%.  </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Dirty Strikes</font> - (3 6 9)  Pre-Requisites(s):  Level 67-68-69. <font color="lime">Ambidexterity, Entrap, Precision of the Pathfinder 3</font>.  Through years of fighting you have learned that often, a killing blow is only followed by rendering your opponent prone.  This AA line gives you a chance to hamstring your opponent, snaring them for 5 ticks.  The chance to land a dirty strike is 3%, 6%, 10%. </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Double Strike</font> - (3 6 9)  Pre-Requisites(s): Level 67-68-69. <font color="lime">Combat Fury 3, Fury of the Ages 3, Ambidexterity, Precision of the Pathfinder 3</font>.  Your coordinated movements wielding 2 weapons have been honed to allow you the ability to strike with both weapons simultaneously, delivering a devastating attack focused on one area.  This AA grants you a chance to land a crippling blow 2%, 5%, 10%. </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Double Cross</font> - (5)  Pre-Requisites(s): Level 66. <font color="lime">Ambidexterity, Double Riposte 3, Flash of Steel 3.</font>  Through years of practice in dual wield, you have learned how to maneuver your opponents into optimal riposte situations.  This AA modifies your ability to riposte by 5%. </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Quickened Blades</font> - (3 6 9)  Pre-Requisite(s): Level 65-66-67. <font color="lime">Ambidexterity, Double Riposte 3, Flash of Steel 3, Double Cross</font>.  Your quickened responses to battle have developed a preternatural ability to predict your opponents next move.  This AA line increases your ability to Parry and Riposte by 3%, 6%, 10%. </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Havoc Strike</font> - (15)  Pre-Requisite(s): Level 70. <font color="lime">Combat Fury 3, Fury of the Ages 3, Double Strike 3</font>.  Your affinity with your weapons has created a phsyic bond, granting you the ability to exchange stamina for an unresistable physic blast to your opponent.  This ability takes 30% of your stamina (yellow mana/endurance) and exchanges it into a direct damage shock into your opponents system, briefly stunning them (1 tick) and stunning yourself for (3 seconds).  The direct damage of this component is equal to 30% of your endurance, and can be affected by the spell casting fury AA line &amp; focus effects MR based. This ability is usable once every 6 minutes.  </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">First Strikes</font> - (5)  Pre-Requisite(s): Level 66. <font color="lime">Ferocity 3</font>.  Your reaction times have increased through years of fighting, granting you heightened reaction in combat.  This AA gives you a chance (2%) in any given round, at a free round of combat, without fear of your opponent striking back. </font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Whirling Blades</font> - (3 6 9)  Pre-Requisite(s): Level 68-69-70. <font color="lime">Combat Fury 3, Fury of the Ages 3, Ambidexterity, Ferocity 3, First Strikes, Quickened Blades 3 &amp; Rapid Strikes 1</font>.  You have developed the ability to overwhelm an opponent through an all-out attack, sacrificing your defense for a burst of killing speed, as you spin in a whirlwind of blades, lashing out at your target. (effect: Spin the Bottle)  This is not stackable with GotF, but can be used in succession after it.  There is no drain on the stamina bar, except for possible increase for extra attacks (yeh, you would get tired wouldn't you?)</font><br /><ul><li><font color="sienna">Level 1 - 5% overhaste, 5% increased chance to critical strike, 25% increased chance to land primary &amp; secondary attack, 25% increased haste, +50 ATK, &amp; 30% increased chance to successfully double attack.  Duration 12 seconds. -40 AC, -5% to parry, riposte, &amp; dodge.  Reuse time 15 minutes. </font></li><li><font color="sienna">Level 2 - 10% overhaste, 10% increased chance to critical strike, 40% increased chance to land primary &amp; secondary attack, 35% increased haste, +100 ATK &amp; 60% increased chance to successfully double attack.  Duration 18 seconds. - 70 AC, -10% to parry, riposte &amp; dodge.  Reuse time 13 minutes. </font></li><li><font color="sienna">Level 3 - 15% overhaste, 25% increased chance to critical strike, 75% increased chance to land primary &amp; secondary attack, 50% increased haste, +150 ATK &amp; 90% increased chance to successfully double attack.  Duration 30 seconds. - 100 AC, -20% to parry, riposte &amp; dodge.  Reuse time 10 minutes.</font></li></ul><font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Hilt Smash</font> - (2 4 6) Pre-Requisite(s) Level 66-68-70. <font color="lime">Ambidexterity, Double Riposte 3, Flash of Steel 3</font>.  Fighting your opponent presents many openings on successful parries for attacks of opportunity.  Often times, these attacks cannot be fully realized, and result in simply smashing an opponent with the hilt of your weapon.  This AA line increases the chance of this type of an attack upon a successful Parry &amp; a failure to Riposte.  This is increased by 3%, 5%, 10%.  This smash briefly stuns an opponent for 0.1 seconds.</font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Rapid Strikes</font> - (3 6 9)  Pre-Requisite(s):  Level 68-69-70. <font color="lime">Ferocity, Quickened Blades, Double Strike 1</font>. See Warriors Flurry line that they received at level 59.<br />
</font><br />
<br />
<font color="sienna"><font color="lime">Shadow Walk</font> - (12)  Pre-Requisite(s) Level 69. Innate Camouflage, Ambidexterity, Ferocity 3, First Strikes, Dirty Strikes, &amp; Quickened Blades 3.  Your ability to keep an opponent occupied and on the defensive, often blinds your opponent to your next move.  This generates a chance to 'shadow walk' or position yourself behind them without their knowing it as they lose sight of you.  This adds a 25% increased chance to Dirty Strike your opponent and an increase of 5% to Double Strike.  ** If  game mechanics can't implement this code. to effectively "shadow step" behind your target... then adding a modified proc <u>Whirlwind</u> (from our PoA quested Windstriker Bow) would be the alternative as the opponent spins about in mass confusion.</font><br />
