</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><br />
<b>Point one, Archery DPS is pretty much risk free. There is virtually no danger to the archer. Melee DPS on the other hand is not. So DPS is not DPS. To have a class that can do rogue damage and generate no agro from a distance is not a good thing for the game. That is what we would have if we were to continue to boost archery DPS.<br />
</b><i><font color="sienna">Are you sure?  It didn't appear to me rangers were anywhere near rogue dps with archery, even in trueshot.  A rogue outparses a ranger during trueshot, even without discing now.  That is to the point of ridiculous.  I dont' see why a ranger can't be 50% of a rogues dps though, with archery on a sustained level, risk/reward.  No group will sit there and let a ranger do that anyway, when they could be more towards the 70% ranger (where we should be) of rogue dps.</font></i><br />
<i></i><br />
<b>Point Two, we do have ideas and thoughts and stuff is already in the works (no I cannot tell you yet) but does that mean we should not talk to you about it? Would you rather we just made changes? Isn't that what got us here? We are not always going to make changes you like but at least you know that you are being heard and for those folks over on the EQlive boards, even you are being heard, the fact that we do not always respond, does not mean we do not read and pass along the good posts. I do have a clue as to what you all are talking about, a large part of what I am trying to do is make sure you have a clue as to what we are talking about. For example, many say that rangers are "broken" our thougt is that they can make it to the high levels and participate in the very high end of EQ just fine, which means, they are not in fact broken. <br />
</b><i><font color="sienna">I disagree here.  I do think rangers are broken.  When I am told to sit outside of a raid, not because I showed up late, not because I can't play my class, but because the class itself isn't desireable, something is broken.  I am being punished for my class, and that, is not right.  Sure, we can exist to a point... but it isn't reaching the Fun-O-Meter for me =)</font></i><br />
<i></i><br />
<b>A big part of the communication issues we are all having, and I have discussed this with the class correspondents at length, is we speak a different language. Broken to you means something entirely different than it does to us. When we read, Spell X is broken because it does not do enough damage, what we might hear is, Spell X does not work the way I want it to, thus I feel it sucks. Had that been presented as, spell X does less damage based on the mana to damage ratio that our other class spells have, well now that is a whole different story and something that our designers can actually look at and measure. It is often hard to measure how much you feel something "Sucks", as I am sure you can imagine.</b><br />
<i><font color="sienna">I'll give you this point.  We are being melodramatic at times, but only because we do feel that our class has taken the proverbial shaft in a place quite uncomfortable.</font></i><br />
<br />
 <br />
I hope I have been clear, concise, and not too snappy in my responses.  I think there is a definite breakdown in communication (no, not the quest!) that has lead us to this point.  Some of it, is due to the noise levels the ranger community is creating.  However, I for one, am willing to work through this, and I hope you, as a representative of SOE, are as well (as it appears you are, otherwise you would not have taken the time to post here).<br />
 <br />
Thanks,</div>
