		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brenlo,<br />
<br />
First I must say thanks for coming to the Glade to hear us out.<br />
<br />
While there are problems with the ranger class; I think the real problem is that theres a difference in what we think is a fix, and what the devs think is an upgrade.<br />
<br />
As others have said; we dont compare to other hybrids when looking at the spells we get from our parent class.  Improving the spells (all of them; nukes, buffs, and heals) that we get from our parent class is a needed fix that would bring us in balance with other classes, it would not be an upgrade.<br />
<br />
Defense and tanking...  Were not looking to be uber tanks; we just want to be able to tank when it hits the fan.  Our defense needs to be looked at in general.  Avoidance should go up and in a perfect world wed dodge more than the plate classes; and less than the leather classes.  On the flip side; our mitigation needs tweeked as we should mitigate worse than plate classes; but better than leather classes.  Currently; that doesnt appear to be the case.  I think these changes too would be viewed as fixes; not upgrades.<br />
<br />
Our melee dps isnt quite where its supposed to be; there are parses all over the net showing that were a bit low on the damage totem pole.  I would think that giving us triple attack would be a relatively easy code change; and easy to get feedback from the players on test.  Im sure there would be tons of rangers who would run the parses and give feedback if that was implemented on Test.  Giving us a melee discipline would make sense and would appear to be simple programmatically.  These two changes Id think would be viewed as fixes and not upgrades; as they would simply be bringing us in line with other classes.<br />
<br />
Issues like the above are what rangers are talking about when they say we are broken.  Resolution of these issues would be viewed by many as fixes to problems; and as such shouldnt require us to give something up in order to get them; including AA points.  We should not be required to spend AA points, or trade something away to get a fix.  An upgrade, yes; but trade something for a fix?<br />
<br />
Fixes like the ones above would affect all rangers; casual gamers and raiders alike.  Once fixes to the simple, obvious problems are out of the way;  we can get to the tricky problems, like what to do with us on raids.<br />
<br />
Finally,  I noticed you said you played a ranger.  I mean no disrespect, but if you played a ranger, and are not upset and confused because rangers did not get a Harmony upgrade in OoW; then we have differing opinions on what its like to be a ranger.<br />
<br />
Thanks again for hearing us out Brenlo.<br />
<br />
Luck and safe travels.<br />
<br />
<br />
Vegah<br />
Ranger of 65 moons<br />
The Renegades; Innoruuk server</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
