		<!-- message -->
		<div>This seems to be a good spot for a first post on the Glade. Serious thread, so fewer headaches from /bonkage <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" class="inlineimg" /><br />
 <br />
<b><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				 <br />
<b>So you lost it [utility]? I do believe you still have it, it is just shared now. </b><br />
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
The more classes that gain our various utility abilities, the more competition we have for spots in groups and raids. Especially since we're only third best at most of what we do, if a group needs someone to do ability x, why not take class y who can do ability x as well as having more DPS? The other issue is that we did not recieve any compensation for further sharing of our utility. Exampes:<br />
 <br />
Monks recieving lull as a yellow mana ability. We could have gotten a tome with a copy/paste version of innerflame in exchange.<br />
 <br />
The introduction of the Berzerker class and their recieving of a superior version of snare.<br />
 <br />
Unlinking disciplines which allows a warrior to use furious and defensive consecutively. Granted, this helped us some too, but to a far less extent, and it doesn't offset the fact that the usefulness of weaponshield in a raid setting is severely diminished. I'm sure warriors could share some of their tanking ability or HP with us in return.<br />
 <br />
Tracking upgrades come to druids and bards an expansion earlier than us and it gets bugged for six months so that they can track better than us until its recent fix. Rogues gain SoS as an AA in PoP allowing them to scout stuff out of our reach.<br />
 <br />
Other utility abilities of ours get diminished due to changes in content and itemization. For example:<br />
 <br />
Healing used to allow me to save a healer's precious mana by topping off everyone's health. Now, increasing mana pools, mana regen, preservation foci, and free heal abilities make this use unnecessary. Our heals certainly aren't powerful enough to keep a tank alive versus higher end exp mobs.<br />
 <br />
Spending 3 AA points gives any 51+ player about half a SOW, and one can equal it by spending more.<br />
 <br />
Snare and root are already split several ways, but these are not essential abilities in many cases. Also, at higher levels, the ability of mobs to summon and/or be immune to the ability altogether makes this less useful.<br />
 <br />
Invis is shared so many ways and is obtainable by anyone through cheap potions. Also, as content grows more difficult, more mobs are able to see through it.<br />
 <br />
These aren't specific to any one class, but the diminishing of our utility's usefulness is a good reason give our DPS-improving AAs and items a boost to compensate. I shall suggest a few "prods" that should help us.<br />
 <br />
- Nuke cast times reduced to 0.5 seconds from a max hasted 1.8. Based off of Sasandra's numbers, our single-cast DPS would be increased to 2078, the best SK single-cast would be 89% the DPS as ours, and we wouldn't lose so much damage from melee, as out of beastlords, shadowknights, and ourselves, we rely on our own melee the most for DPS. This closes the DPS gap some, and with some more melee boosts, it would put us at a closer third than we are now.<br />
 <br />
- Copy and paste the new harmony from druids. This alone would eliminate 30% of our complaints. We'd be solidly in the second tier of pulling outdoors again, like we always were.<br />
 <br />
- Autofire archery would eliminate repetitive stress injury and give a slight boost to ranged DPS since it would no longer be clientside and based on lag and the player's timing. This would reduce complaining a further 20% since this would send the message that archery is not being ignored to those who prefer that method of combat.<br />
 <br />
- Auspice needs to be improved to make more of a difference during its 36 second duration. Improving DPS by about 20% for those affected would be fair.<br />
 <br />
Four prods, two requiring no creativity whatsoever, and the amount of complaints could be cut in half. Toss us some of the stuff I mentioned earlier as repayment for shared utility, and the SOE ranger forums would probably become quite tame.</b></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
