		<div>I started playing a Ranger back in 1999. Loved the class and haven't played any other since. What I always liked about the Ranger is its versatility, but as of late our versatility was taken from us.<br />
 <br />
As stated in previous posts, Harmony line of spells have simply become unuseful because of the level restrictions/class restrictions/and resist levels against it. Also stated previously how we used to be expert outdoor pullers. Many a time I was asked to pull outdoor because of Harmony and also the ability to snare a mob as it came back to the group. Fast forward a few years and monk, bards, rogues, paladins etc get a Lull line of spells that work indoors and voila........one of our class defining versatilities go out the window.<br />
 <br />
Another issue is also spells that do damage against summoned beings.....err where are these creatures......cause I havent seen many of them. Sure maybe the Hole back in its day or at one time against Rumblecrush, but look around Sony, you gave us a decidely useless line of spells.<br />
 <br />
Spells to increase or modify:<br />
1: Harmony (indoor and outdoor)<br />
2: Heals<br />
3: You can have the summoned spells back<br />
4: A desirable group buff spell or AA (yar we got Auspice but it has small cast range and doesn;t land on certain folks because of other buffs)<br />
 <br />
AA's:<br />
1: If our Archery wont be increased no time soon, then I request that you take away all three of those useless Archery aa's i.e. Frost Arrow etc...and maybe give us one good one, like a burst melee triple attack dps with a lower reuse timer.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Alot has been said over all these posts, and you said you have listened......but other than fixing LoS I haven't seen many of our well thought out suggestions implemented yet.<br />
 <br />
One last thing also, for some reason I am getting the sneaky suspicion that the Hybrid Penalty Modifier was back in place, is this true cause I do remember the 'Hell' levels and it sure feels like it to me.<br />
 <br />
Thank you for your time and patience with all of us. We desire feedback is all we are asking.<br />
 <br />
P.S. And for godsakes, what do we do with Corun's notes......please tell us !!!!</div>
