	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>Filtering through the Static</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#333300" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Brenlo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Honestly, that board is currently filled with so much static that it is impossible to have any meaningful discourse.  For now, I will post here and converse with you folks.  Should the folks there follow me in an attempt to disrupt this board, I will move elsewhere.  Should they decide that they can and will be reasonable, I will post on that forum as well.  Until such time, you are stuck with me here.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
Dear Brenlo:<br />
<br />
I was tempted to start a new thread for this, titled "Filtering through the Static" but I was afraid you might only be watching this thread and miss it.  On the other hand, I am afraid that you might miss it because there is bound to be a lot of static here in this particular thread now that you have made an appearance.  If you see this, I would appreciate a response, so at least I know it has been seen.<br />
<br />
I've been getting a little hot under the collar on the boards myself recently, and this post is going to be my attempt to step back and come at this from a different angle, which I suspect is exactly what you are trying to do by posting here.  Let's start this with a clean slate then, shall we?<br />
<br />
In order to answer your questions, I am going to be quoting a lot of stuff from the EQLive boards.  That's why I wanted to title it "Filtering through the Static."  Because this "baby with the bathwater" approach to starting all over again in a new place means a lot of very valid stuff is being missed.<br />
<br />
I direct you to the following posts, all of which have suggested, requested, or demanded a developer take some time to interface with the customers at EQLive.<br />
<br />
6/14/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=2816" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=2816</a><br />
6/10/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=2620#M2620" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...e.id=2620#M2620</a><br />
7/09/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=3853" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=3853</a><br />
7/13/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=4332" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=4332</a><br />
7/11/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=4036" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=4036</a><br />
7/30/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=5861#M5861" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...e.id=5861#M5861</a><br />
8/06/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=6529" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=6529</a><br />
8/16/04 -- the Q&amp;A<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=7513" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=7513</a><br />
8/26/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=8578" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=8578</a><br />
8/31/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=9015" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=9015</a><br />
9/02/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=9376" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=9376</a><br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=9445" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=9445</a><br />
9/08/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=9892" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=9892</a><br />
9/15/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=10898" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=10898</a><br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=10927" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=10927</a><br />
9/16/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11578" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11578</a><br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rangers&amp;message.id=4195" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=4195</a><br />
9/18/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11798" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11798</a><br />
9/19/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11833" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11833</a><br />
9/20/04<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rangers&amp;message.id=4417" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=4417</a><br />
<br />
There you have it.  20 separate posts and/or threads over the course of over 3 months, all asking for the same thing: <b>communication</b>. <br />
<br />
If you TRULY desire to work in our best interests, then you need to start communicating with us.  You need to do THERE what you have done here.  In exchange, things will get better there, I virtually guarantee it.<br />
<br />
And before you say, "Well, I made a couple posts saying 'let's move on from here' so I have been communicating" I will say straight out, that is NOT communication.<br />
<br />
When you respond to something someone has written, the actual context of what they have said, addressing the specific points they have made, THAT is communication.  Your response to me that is quoted at the beginning of this post...that is actually communication.  You read what I wrote, and you answered the specific point I made.<br />
<br />
Your posts on the boards this past week haven't done that.  You were making declarations, not communicating.  You were speaking, but you weren't listening.  You weren't answering what the people on the boards had to say...you just made sweeping statements from On High.  That's not communicating.<br />
<br />
IF you were to go back to the EQLive boards and interact with those threads the same way you have been interacting with responses on this one, then you would be communicating.  And I guarantee, within 24 hours you would see a world of change.<br />
<br />
In short, I highly encourage you to go back to those boards and be MORE available and communicative, rather than coming to these boards and hiding from the people there.  People who find it easy to snark at you behind your back (i.e. when you haven't posted for a while and show no indications of being inclined to do so) will have a lot harder time being discourteous if they know you are there and reading.  In short, a consistent and palpable presence on the boards, and actual live interaction, would clean the EQLive boards up in a real hurry.  You are going about getting useful communication accomplished in the wrong way by simply changing venues.  You need to change the atmosphere in THAT venue instead.<br />
<br />
[[Now that that is out of the way, let's move on to the second part, which addresses ranger concerns in general.<br />
<br />
I will start with the points you have made in this specific thread.  Then I will move onto points which are being neglected on the EQLive boards.  I am going to do a lot of quoting here, so that I can address specific points and therefore emphasize the communication angle of things.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Brenlo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">
Now that aside, there are no plans to nerf archery folks. The current plan is to focus on ranger melee.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
Ok, I think most of us, even those of us who like archery (of which I will freely admit I am one) can accept that.  HOWEVER...<br />
<br />
I direct your attention to the following posts over at EQLive, and will quote snippets for the sake of brevity:<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rangers&amp;message.id=4195" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=4195</a><br />
<i>prove to me that you ARE actually putting some thought into this, and that in another 6 months or even 3 years, you won't turn around with the Next Great Expansion and say, "doh, we goofed!  Rangers are supposed to be ARCHERS!  You've just wasted dozens of AAs on melee skills that are useless, but here, have a bow with a really neat particle affect and smile!"</i><br />
<br />
Ok, the above is the truly germane quote of that entire post.  I think most rangers feel SOE has done a pretty big flip-flop here.  Rangers have a major case of schizophrenia right now (see this post, which addresses the various stages of a ranger's life span and how they can lead to various misinterpretations of what a ranger's role should be: <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11882" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11882</a>)<br />
<br />
The archery genie is out of the bottle, and there is quite simply no way of putting it back in short of using the dreaded "N" word where the "archery sweet-spot" is concerned.  SOE included aspects in the game that led a certain amount of players (even, I daresay, the majority of players) to believe that archery was supposed to be a ranger's role.  Here are some of those aspects:<br />
<br />
One of our first quests is an archery-centric quest.<br />
The tradeskill rangers get prodded toward by early game quests (and even Epic 2.0) is fletching.<br />
The existing class description for Rangers lists archery ahead of other combat forms, leading people to believe that archery is our primary form of attack.<br />
Melee classes hacking away at the butt of a mob are a dime a dozen, so archery makes people feel unique, like they have something different to offer.<br />
<br />
Now, I'm not trying to start the archery/melee debate all over again. The validity of these assumptions is not the question that we need to be dealing with, so there's no sense in telling me how "wrong" people are for placing stock in these assumptions.  It's not about right or wrong.  People feel how they feel, and you can't simply say, "you feel the wrong way, now turn it around."  It's not that easy.<br />
<br />
So, Brenlo, IF SOE wants to move in the direction of melee, ignoring archery is NOT the way to do it, certainly not if you want it done in a peaceful, orderly fashion.  People at this point have too large an emotional stake in the issue to let it go just because you say, "because I say so, that's why."<br />
<br />
Here's another quote from the boards to consider:<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11874#M11874" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...id=11874#M11874</a><br />
<i>We want to be able to customize our character in such a way as to make it "different but equal."  That means trade-offs.  Most of us are prepared to accept those.  We do a certain percentage less damage in exchange for a certain amount of decreased inherent risk.  Fine.  No problem.<br />
<br />
But that is NOT what SOE is offering.  In the dreaded "all encounters" statement, the Devs didn't say:<br />
<br />
(Dev notes - This is how it should be. In order to use archery, you accept an inherent lack of DPS in exchange for your lack of exposure to riposte, DS, rampage, and AoE damage.  Archery will remain in proportion to melee but will retain a slight DPS disadvantage as its tradeoff (85-90% of melee damage will be considered optimal), and we will be from time to time offering unique archery-only abilities and itemization that will keep archery in step with melee as regards its viability as a combat alternative, so that as melee continues to improve, so will archery, again, in proportion to melee.)<br />
<br />
If the Devs had said that, do you think ANY of this discussion would be going on now?  I can almost guarantee none of it would be.  We "archery rangers" would have shut up and went away happily anticipating what the devs had in store for us for OOW and beyond, or we would have focused our efforts on other ranger insuffiencies, such as, oh, I dunno, the lack of a friggin HARMONY upgrade!<br />
</i><br />
<br />
So this whole movement toward migrating rangers back toward a melee-centric class has been handled very badly from the get-go.  Had it been handled with more sensitivity regarding the time and emotional investment people have put into their characters, it could have gone much more smoothly.  The text of the initial "all encounters" statement DOES lead people to believe that archery is being nerfed and/or will be neglected into oblivion.<br />
<br />
Rather than telling people, "just focus on melee" why can't you simply go to the boards and make a statement like what the poster at EQLive hypothesized in the above-quoted snippet?  Isn't much easier to try to smooth ruffled feathers than simply digging your heels in and telling people they are being too extreme?  Why not try to calm things down rather than inciting them more?<br />
<br />
All that is needed here is some diplomacy.  And diplomacy has been sorely lacking in this entire affair.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
