<br />
No one has ever said this.  I have been scanning the last 6 months of posts for hours and cannot find a single instance of this.<br />
<br />
Right now, however, rogues who are NOT using their disciplines can do over twice the melee damage of comparably equipped rangers (who, of course, have no melee disciplines.)  This is very out of balance.  We don't want DPS rivalling rogues.  However, I think their having twice our DPS is extremely excessive and things need to be brought back into balance, so SOME DPS increase is an absolute must.<br />
<br />
Allow me to direct your attention to the following posts:<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=4522#M4522" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...e.id=4522#M4522</a><br />
<i>If the endgame rogue is doing 425 DPS...<br />
...the endgame Monk should be doing 375-400<br />
...the endgame ranger should be doing 350-375 with melee<br />
...the endgame ranger should be doing 325-350 with archery</i><br />
<br />
Now, those numbers may be a bit off, but the theory of the scale seems to hold pretty true.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=11882" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...essage.id=11882</a><br />
<i>3) MELEE DPS<br />
Ranger melee DPS needs to be drastically increased to bring it in line with other melee-centric DPS classes, such as rogues and monks. Ideally, if a rogue is the undisputed DPS king, a monk should do maybe 90% of a rogue's DPS, and a Ranger should do 80% of a rogues DPS while meleeing. Melee disciplines are needed for burst DPS that will also scale in proportion to rogue and monk burst DPS.<br />
4) ARCHERY DPS<br />
Ranger archery DPS needs to scale in proportion to our melee DPS. It should never been any more than 85-90% of melee dps, EXCEPT when Trueshot is active. If it is felt that archery needs to have more of a "cost", tie it to the Endurance bar and give archery DPS an expense. If you do that, however, archery damage should be higher in its proportion to melee damage, say, 90-95% instead.</i><br />
<br />
and later in that same thread:<br />
<i>I would think monks 80% of rogues, and rangers 70% of rogues melee dmg.  That is somewhere in the line that they stated from long ago.<br />
</i><br />
<br />
<i>I remember long time ago from "Verant", saying that:<br />
 Rogue is like 1.5 of a Warrior,<br />
 Monk is like 1.35 of a Warrior,<br />
 Ranger should be something 1.3 of a warrior.</i><br />
<br />
Here's my suggestion.  Let's go with the 80% of rogue DPS model, just as an example.  That means, if rogues are doing melee DPS of 400 without using their disciplines, comparably equipped rangers need to be able to do melee DPS of 320.  Rangers don't even do close to that right now.  Furthermore, if rogues have the ability to do burst disciplined damage of up to 600 DPS (I've seen parses that indicate this is the case) then Rangers need to be able to do burst damage of 480 DPS.  Trueshot does between 400-500, so that puts us in the target range, however, for one thing, it's not a melee discipline, and if SOE truly wants to encourage rangers to use melee, then we need melee disciplines.  Furthermore, Trueshot has a 72 minute reuse timer.  Whatever burst damage disciplines rangers get to bring them in proportion to rogues need to have timers that are as frequent as rogue discipline timers are.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
