<br />
Aside from the fact that no one has ever asked for rogue DPS, let's address the utility issue.<br />
<br />
I direct your attention to this post, which is the second half of a two-part post, specifically addressing ranger utility:<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=5981#M5981" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...e.id=5981#M5981</a><br />
<br />
You say that in order to increase our DPS, you would have to take away our utility.  The problem is, our utility is already severely flawed and underpowered, almost to the point of being useless.  So I just have to ask...what utility are you referring to?<br />
<br />
Our snare and root spells need to have some severe adjustments made to their resistability.  Right now, our crowd control abilities are really suffering, therefore we are beginning to lose this "utility."<br />
<br />
Our nukes and DoTs also need resist mods, shorter casting times, and shorter recast times.  We have to memorize too many of them to be able to chain nuke because of the 30 second recast time, which means our mana goes practically unused far too frequently.  The cast time is long enough that once our melee DPS gets high enough, casting them COSTS us DPS, especially when resist and mitigation rates are factored in.  So we have no real utility as a nuke/DoT caster.<br />
<br />
Our Harmony only goes through level 65, and we have been told flat out that there are no plans to improve Harmony for the ranger class (<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=3800" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...message.id=3800</a>) therefore our utility as a pulling class is in jeopardy, especially considering several other classes got improved lulls/pacification/harmony with the last expansion and we didn't.<br />
<br />
I won't even address buffs, heals, and agro-reduction.  They are all severely sub-par as well.  Read the post I just linked above for more detail on those aspects.<br />
<br />
Furthermore, our utility is being farmed out left and right to yellow-mana classes.  Zerkers have snare and group ATK buffs.  Rogues have a better ability to scout because tracking has been nerfed by the inclusion of untrackable mobs and the preponderance of mobs that can see invisible but can't see through SoS.  Monks have lull which now makes them better pullers not only indoors, but outdoors as well, and snare as well.<br />
<br />
In a nutshell, these changes absolutely NEED to happen before you can speak of our "utility" being a factor in what damage we should theoretically be able to do.<br />
<br />
Our utility is the reason why we are asking for 70-80% of a rogues damage, instead of 100%.  We recognize that there is a tradeoff necessary.  The problem is, both are severely under where they need to be.  BOTH need to be tweaked upwards.  I refer you to this post:<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=4549#M4549" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...e.id=4549#M4549</a><br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
