<br />
Let's say a rogue is 100% DPS.<br />
Let's say an enchanter is 100% utility.<br />
<br />
Rangers should be 70-80% DPS and 20-30% utility.  Archery damage should be 85-90% of ranger melee damage as the tradeoff for decreased risk.  If you want to attach a "cost" to archery (like making special archery skills dependent upon endurance, as has been suggested many, many times over) then the damage should be increased as well, maybe 90-95% of ranger melee, since that damage is no longer "free."<br />
<br />
This means, again, if a rogue is doing 400 DPS, a ranger needs to be doing 320 DPS.  The disparity between the two needs to be filled with the ability to scout, pull, buff, and crowd control more effectively.<br />
<br />
