		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brenlo,<br />
<br />
There are 2 primary problems I see with rangers right now.<br />
<br />
Number 1:<br />
Our dps whether it be by whatever means, is low. I don't think we should have to spend 200 AA to get the needed DPS boost either. If you are going to boost ranger DPS please do it across the board via our damage table. Somewhere closer to monks than warriors I think would be about right. That doesn't mean I want you to take away the ability to improve DPS with AAs either, we want to be higher DPS at 0 AA than a Warrior is with 0AA and we want to spread that gap even wider at 200 AA vs 200AA.<br />
<br />
Number 2:<br />
You say our utility is now "Shared" and not "taken away" but every time you "share" our utility with another class you do infact take away a little bit of reason for someone to invite us to a group or desire us for a raid, when they can just move along to the "Shared" class, who might do other things that they need to. For example a CLERIC can pull better than I can in outdoor OOW zones because they got a Pacify upgrade, and I got a reverse jolt buff. Why get the ranger? The enchanter got a pulling utility upgrade, the ench can pull and mez too. That ranger can't even pull OUTDOOR OoW zones.. And indoors? Forget about it.<br />
<br />
So feedback? Here you go brother,<br />
<br />
Give us more mele DPS. (Something flashy and cool like a duelist type AA ability, or an AA that allows us to Crit for 20 seconds strait).<br />
<br />
Buffs:<br />
Brenlo man, something has got to be done about <b>SOP</b> and <b>SoT</b>, the upgrades on these do not scale well at all. Please do not do some ATK=X number of HP calculation to ballance it with the BSS line. Don't do that, just look at the buffs and ask around, ask 200 people, no, ask 200 rogues, would you rather have BSS or SoT and I'll be damned if 80% of them don't ask for BSS. Man that's not right!<br />
Also, our SOP line does not look good in OoW. Man that spell barely got any upgrade at all, you gotta fix that.<br />
<br />
Finally, Utility:<br />
<br />
Give us an indoor lull that works on mobs at least up to 65<br />
<br />
Give us an outdoor Harmony that works on mobs up to level 69 or 70 (69 even would be way better than what we have now)<br />
<br />
Some have mentioned an outdoor only Fading Memories type ability. How about looking into something like that? I'm not sure about that one but if you guys can squeeze it in after the other stuff go for it. Besides, we wouldn't be taking that away from bards, we'd just be "sharing" right?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Upgrades that I think we can sacrifice to get these changes made:<br />
<br />
Do the things I mentioned ablove and leave our <b>healing</b> alone and I'll be a happy camper.<br />
<br />
Do the things I mentioned above and leave our <b>tanking</b> status alone and I'll be happy camper.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
